{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868063411,"sessionID":"ses_28604276bffe3aMZ50oXCQRdNM","part":{"id":"prt_d79fc2983001nTWz1Qw2qNYlKz","messageID":"msg_d79fc1533001KGDxk3AFA2CLqX","sessionID":"ses_28604276bffe3aMZ50oXCQRdNM","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_075a3ce141e7457b953bbea9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec-ar-021.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec-ar-021.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification — AR-021: CLI build 命令\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n6: **Language:** Python  \n7: **Size:** M  \n8: **Type:** Implementation of build command for container image building\n9: \n10: **Base Specs:** cli-toolkit/design.md, cli-toolkit/spec.md\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Requirements & Scenarios\n15: \n16: ### REQ-021.1: Build Command CLI Interface\n17: \n18: **Requirement:** The system SHALL implement the `build` Typer subcommand with options for workspace path, proxy configuration, cloud provider selection, output path, and verbose logging.\n19: \n20: #### Scenario: Build command registration\n21: - **GIVEN** the Typer app is initialized\n22: - **WHEN** the CLI loads\n23: - **THEN** the `build` subcommand SHALL be registered as `agentcube build`\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Default workspace resolution\n26: - **GIVEN** user runs `agentcube build` without `-f` flag\n27: - **WHEN** the command executes\n28: - **THEN** workspace SHALL resolve to current directory `\".\"`\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Custom workspace path\n31: - **GIVEN** user specifies `-f /path/to/workspace`\n32: - **WHEN** the command executes\n33: - **THEN** workspace SHALL resolve to the provided absolute or relative path\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Proxy configuration via flag\n36: - **GIVEN** user specifies `-p http://proxy:port` or `--proxy http://proxy:port`\n37: - **WHEN** the command executes\n38: - **THEN** proxy SHALL be passed to build options for dependency resolution\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Cloud provider selection\n41: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--cloud-provider huawei`\n42: - **WHEN** the command executes\n43: - **THEN** cloud provider SHALL override default build mode to `cloud`\n44: \n45: #### Scenario: Output path for build artifacts\n46: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--output /path/to/output`\n47: - **WHEN** the command completes\n48: - **THEN** build artifacts SHALL be copied or linked to the output path\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Command-level verbose logging\n51: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--verbose` on build command\n52: - **WHEN** the command executes\n53: - **THEN** logging level SHALL be DEBUG for build operation only\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ### REQ-021.2: BuildRuntime Integration\n58: \n59: **Requirement:** The system SHALL instantiate `BuildRuntime` with verbose flag and invoke `build()` method with workspace path and options.\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: BuildRuntime instantiation\n62: - **GIVEN** build command is invoked\n63: - **WHEN** command handler runs\n64: - **THEN** `BuildRuntime(verbose=verbose)` SHALL be instantiated\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: Pass options to BuildRuntime.build\n67: - **GIVEN** CLI options are parsed\n68: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime.build()` is called\n69: - **THEN** options dict SHALL include: `proxy`, `cloud_provider`, `output`, and any metadata overrides\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Handle BuildRuntime exceptions\n72: - **GIVEN** `BuildRuntime.build()` raises an exception\n73: - **WHEN** exception is caught\n74: - **THEN** `_handle_error(e, \"build\", verbose)` SHALL be invoked\n75: \n76: #### Scenario: Display build success\n77: - **GIVEN** build completes successfully\n78: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime.build()` returns result dict\n79: - **THEN** CLI SHALL print success message with image name, tag, and build time using Rich formatting\n80: \n81: ---\n82: \n83: ### REQ-021.3: Build Mode Resolution\n84: \n85: **Requirement:** The system SHALL determine build mode (local vs cloud) from metadata, with CLI `--cloud-provider` flag taking precedence.\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: Default to local build\n88: - **GIVEN** metadata has `build_mode: local` or no build_mode specified\n89: - **WHEN** `--cloud-provider` is not provided\n90: - **THEN** build mode SHALL be `local`\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: Cloud provider overrides to cloud mode\n93: - **GIVEN** user specifies `--cloud-provider huawei`\n94: - **WHEN** build mode is resolved\n95: - **THEN** build mode SHALL be `cloud` regardless of metadata\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Cloud mode requires cloud provider\n98: - **GIVEN** metadata has `build_mode: cloud`\n99: - **WHEN** no `--cloud-provider` is specified\n100: - **THEN** system SHALL raise error requiring cloud provider name\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ### REQ-021.4: Local Docker Build Flow\n105: \n106: **Requirement:** The system SHALL execute local Docker build using `DockerService` when build mode is `local`.\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: Docker availability check\n109: - **GIVEN** build mode is `local`\n110: - **WHEN** build starts\n111: - **THEN** `DockerService.check_docker_available()` SHALL be called first\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: Docker not available error\n114: - **GIVEN** Docker daemon is not running\n115: - **WHEN** `check_docker_available()` fails\n116: - **THEN** `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")` SHALL be raised\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: Build image with DockerService\n119: - **GIVEN** Docker is available\n120: - **WHEN** local build proceeds\n121: - **THEN** `DockerService.build_image()` SHALL be called with:\n122:   - `dockerfile_path`: workspace/Dockerfile\n123:   - `context_path`: workspace\n124:   - `image_name`: `{agent_name}`\n125:   - `tag`: `{version}` or `latest`\n126:   - `build_args`: proxy settings if provided\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Image tagging convention\n129: - **GIVEN** metadata version is `1.2.3`\n130: - **WHEN** image is built\n131: - **THEN** image tag SHALL be `{agent_name}:1.2.3`\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: Fallback tag when no version\n134: - **GIVEN** metadata has no version\n135: - **WHEN** image is built\n136: - **THEN** image tag SHALL default to `{agent_name}:latest`\n137: \n138: ---\n139: \n140: ### REQ-021.5: Version Increment Logic\n141: \n142: **Requirement:** The system SHALL increment version before local build and revert on failure.\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: Patch version increment\n145: - **GIVEN** current version is `1.2.3`\n146: - **WHEN** build starts\n147: - **THEN** version SHALL become `1.2.4` before build\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: Minor version increment\n150: - **GIVEN** current version is `1.2.0` and user requests minor bump\n151: - **WHEN** build starts\n152: - **THEN** version SHALL become `1.3.0`\n153: \n154: #### Scenario: Major version increment\n155: - **GIVEN** current version is `1.0.0` and user requests major bump\n156: - **WHEN** build starts\n157: - **THEN** version SHALL become `2.0.0`\n158: \n159: #### Scenario: Pre-release version handling\n160: - **GIVEN** current version is `1.0.0-alpha.1`\n161: - **WHEN** build starts\n162: - **THEN** version SHALL increment pre-release to `1.0.0-alpha.2`\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: Version revert on build failure\n165: - **GIVEN** build fails after version increment\n166: - **WHEN** error is caught\n167: - **THEN** metadata version SHALL be reverted to original value\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: Version string fallback\n170: - **GIVEN** version is not semver format (e.g., `v1.0`)\n171: - **WHEN** increment is attempted\n172: - **THEN** system SHALL append `.1` (e.g., `v1.0.1`) or use `{version}-1` fallback\n173: \n174: ---\n175: \n176: ### REQ-021.6: Cloud Build Flow\n177: \n178: **Requirement:** The system SHALL trigger cloud build when build mode is `cloud` and cloud provider is specified.\n179: \n180: #### Scenario: Cloud build prerequisite validation\n181: - **GIVEN** build mode is `cloud`\n182: - **WHEN** build starts\n183: - **THEN** system SHALL validate cloud provider credentials/configuration\n184: \n185: #### Scenario: Huawei cloud provider\n186: - **GIVEN** `--cloud-provider huawei`\n187: - **WHEN** cloud build is triggered\n188: - **THEN** system SHALL use Huawei Cloud Container Registry API\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: Cloud provider not supported\n191: - **GIVEN** `--cloud-provider unknown-provider`\n192: - **WHEN** build starts\n193: - **THEN** system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"Unsupported cloud provider: unknown-provider\")`\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: Cloud build status polling\n196: - **GIVEN** cloud build is triggered\n197: - **WHEN** build is in progress\n198: - **THEN** system SHALL poll build status with progress indicator\n199: \n200: #### Scenario: Cloud build timeout\n201: - **GIVEN** cloud build exceeds timeout (default 600s)\n202: - **WHEN** polling continues\n203: - **THEN** system SHALL raise `TimeoutError(\"Cloud build exceeded timeout\")`\n204: \n205: ---\n206: \n207: ### REQ-021.7: Build Validation Prerequisites\n208: \n209: **Requirement:** The system SHALL validate workspace prerequisites before build.\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: Dockerfile existence check\n212: - **GIVEN** build is about to start\n213: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime._validate_build_prerequisites()` runs\n214: - **THEN** system SHALL check for Dockerfile in workspace\n215: \n216: #### Scenario: Missing Dockerfile\n217: - **GIVEN** no Dockerfile exists in workspace\n218: - **WHEN** validation runs\n219: - **THEN** system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"Dockerfile not found in workspace\")`\n220: \n221: #### Scenario: Metadata validation\n222: - **GIVEN** build is about to start\n223: - **WHEN** prerequisites are validated\n224: - **THEN** system SHALL verify `agent_metadata.yaml` exists and is valid\n225: \n226: #### Scenario: Image name validation\n227: - **GIVEN** agent_name contains invalid characters\n228: - **WHEN** build starts\n229: - **THEN** system SHALL sanitize or reject invalid image names per Docker naming rules\n230: \n231: ---\n232: \n233: ### REQ-021.8: Build Output and Reporting\n234: \n235: **Requirement:** The system SHALL report build results with image details, build time, and next steps.\n236: \n237: #### Scenario: Build success output\n238: - **GIVEN** build completes successfully\n239: - **WHEN** result is returned\n240: - **THEN** CLI SHALL print:\n241:   ```\n242:   ✓ Build completed successfully\n243:   Image: {image_name}:{tag}\n244:   Image ID: {image_id}\n245:   Size: {image_size}\n246:   Build time: {build_time}s\n247:   ```\n248: \n249: #### Scenario: Build result metadata update\n250: - **GIVEN** build succeeds\n251: - **WHEN** `_update_build_metadata()` runs\n252: - **THEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` SHALL be updated with image info (name, tag, id, size)\n253: \n254: #### Scenario: Verbose build logs\n255: - **GIVEN** `--verbose` is true\n256: - **WHEN** build runs\n257: - **THEN** Docker build logs SHALL be streamed to console\n258: \n259: #### Scenario: Next step guidance\n260: - **GIVEN** build succeeds\n261: - **WHEN** output is printed\n262: - **THEN** CLI SHALL suggest next command: `agentcube publish` with appropriate flags\n263: \n264: ---\n265: \n266: ### REQ-021.9: Proxy Configuration\n267: \n268: **Requirement:** The system SHALL support proxy configuration for dependency resolution during build.\n269: \n270: #### Scenario: Proxy via CLI flag\n271: - **GIVEN** user specifies `-p http://proxy:port`\n272: - **WHEN** build runs\n273: - **THEN** proxy SHALL be set as `build_arg` for Docker build\n274: \n275: #### Scenario: Proxy environment variable fallback\n276: - **GIVEN** no `-p` flag but `HTTP_PROXY` env var is set\n277: - **WHEN** build runs\n278: - **THEN** proxy SHALL be read from environment\n279: \n280: #### Scenario: Proxy for pip installs\n281: - **GIVEN** Python workspace with requirements.txt\n282: - **WHEN** build processes dependencies\n283: - **THEN** pip install SHALL use `--proxy` flag if proxy is configured\n284: \n285: #### Scenario: Proxy for maven builds\n286: - **GIVEN** Java workspace with pom.xml\n287: - **WHEN** build processes dependencies\n288: - **THEN** maven settings.xml SHALL include proxy configuration\n289: \n290: ---\n291: \n292: ## Data Types\n293: \n294: ```python\n295: # Build command options\n296: class BuildOptions(TypedDict, total=False):\n297:     workspace: str\n298:     proxy: Optional[str]\n299:     cloud_provider: Optional[str]\n300:     output: Optional[str]\n301:     verbose: bool\n302: \n303: # Build result structure\n304: class BuildResult(TypedDict):\n305:     image_name: str\n306:     image_tag: str\n307:     image_id: str\n308:     image_size: str\n309:     build_time: str\n310:     build_mode: str\n311:     cloud_provider: Optional[str]\n312: ```\n313: \n314: ---\n315: \n316: ## CLI Flags Summary\n317: \n318: | Flag | Short | Type | Default | Description |\n319: |------|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n320: | `--workspace` | `-f` | str | `\".\"` | Path to agent workspace |\n321: | `--proxy` | `-p` | Optional[str] | None | Proxy URL for dependencies |\n322: | `--cloud-provider` | - | Optional[str] | None | Cloud provider name (huawei, etc.) |\n323: | `--output` | - | Optional[str] | None | Output path for artifacts |\n324: | `--verbose` | - | bool | False | Enable detailed logging |\n325: \n326: ---\n327: \n328: ## Environment Variables\n329: \n330: | Variable | Description | Default |\n331: |----------|-------------|---------|\n332: | `HTTP_PROXY` | HTTP proxy for builds | - |\n333: | `HTTPS_PROXY` | HTTPS proxy for builds | - |\n334: | `DOCKER_HOST` | Docker daemon socket | system default |\n335: \n336: ---\n337: \n338: ## Error Codes\n339: \n340: | Error | Exit Code | Message |\n341: |-------|-----------|---------|\n342: | Docker unavailable | 1 | \"Docker is not available or not running\" |\n343: | Missing Dockerfile | 1 | \"Dockerfile not found in workspace\" |\n344: | Invalid cloud provider | 1 | \"Unsupported cloud provider: {name}\" |\n345: | Build failure | 1 | \"Build failed: {detail}\" |\n346: | Cloud build timeout | 1 | \"Cloud build exceeded timeout ({duration}s)\" |\n347: | Version increment failure | 1 | \"Failed to increment version: {detail}\" |\n348: \n349: ---\n350: \n351: ## Dependencies\n352: \n353: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n354: |---------|---------|---------|\n355: | `typer[all]` | >=0.9.0 | CLI framework |\n356: | `pydantic` | >=2.0.0 | Data validation |\n357: | `docker` | >=6.0.0 | Docker SDK |\n358: | `rich` | >=13.0.0 | Output formatting |\n359: | `semver` | >=3.0.0 | Version parsing |\n360: | `pyyaml` | >=6.0 | Metadata handling |\n361: \n362: ---\n363: \n364: ## Acceptance Checklist\n365: \n366: - [ ] `agentcube/cli/main.py` — build command registered with Typer\n367: - [ ] `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` — BuildRuntime class implemented\n368: - [ ] `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` — DockerService for local builds\n369: - [ ] `agentcube/services/cloud_providers/` — Cloud provider implementations\n370: - [ ] Version increment logic with rollback on failure\n371: - [ ] Proxy configuration via flag and environment\n372: - [ ] Build prerequisites validation (Dockerfile, metadata)\n373: - [ ] Success/failure output with Rich formatting\n374: - [ ] Verbose mode streams build logs\n375: - [ ] Error handling with appropriate exit codes\n376: - [ ] Next step guidance after successful build\n377: - [ ] Code coverage >= 80% for build path\n378: \n379: ---\n380: \n381: ## Open Questions\n382: \n383: 1. Should build command support `--tag` override for custom image tags?\n384: 2. Should multi-platform builds (`--platform`) be supported in initial release?\n385: 3. Should build cache options (`--no-cache`, `--cache-from`) be exposed?\n\n(End of file - total 385 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification — AR-021: CLI build 命令\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Type:** Implementation of build command for container image building\n\n**Base Specs:** cli-toolkit/design.md, cli-toolkit/spec.md\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-021.1: Build Command CLI Interface\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL implement the `build` Typer subcommand with options for workspace path, proxy configuration, cloud provider selection, output path, and verbose logging.\n\n#### Scenario: Build command registration","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec-ar-021.md","time":{"start":1775868063399,"end":1775868063409}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868063417,"sessionID":"ses_28604276bffe3aMZ50oXCQRdNM","part":{"id":"prt_d79fc2486001IOtHNd3HV7Erd2","messageID":"msg_d79fc1533001KGDxk3AFA2CLqX","sessionID":"ses_28604276bffe3aMZ50oXCQRdNM","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_88da5aec3f90472896b356ed","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-002 — CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义 Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define the CodeInterpreter CRD type implementation including Go API types, validation, CRD manifests, client-go library, informers, and listers for the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreter API type definition\n10: \n11: The system SHALL define `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` with `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterSpec` types. `CodeInterpreterSpec` SHALL include `runtimeRef` (string), `code` (string), `language` (string), `executionPolicy` (ExecutionPolicy), and `resources` (ResourceQuota). `CodeInterpreter` SHALL embed `metav1.TypeMeta` and `metav1.ObjectMeta`.\n12: \n13: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter type registration\n14: \n15: - **GIVEN** the `v1alpha1` package is imported\n16: - **WHEN** `SchemeBuilder.Register(&CodeInterpreter{}, &CodeInterpreterList{})` is called during init\n17: - **THEN** `CodeInterpreter` SHALL be registered in the scheme with `Kind = \"CodeInterpreter\"`, `APIVersion = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\"`\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Runtime reference binding\n20: \n21: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter YAML with `spec.runtimeRef: \"python-3.11\"`\n22: - **WHEN** the CodeInterpreter is parsed by the scheme\n23: - **THEN** `CodeInterpreter.Spec.RuntimeRef` SHALL be populated with the runtime name string\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Code field parsing\n26: \n27: - **GIVEN** `spec.code` contains Python code string\n28: - **WHEN** the CodeInterpreter is deserialized\n29: - **THEN** `CodeInterpreter.Spec.Code` SHALL contain the exact code string\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Language specification\n32: \n33: - **GIVEN** `spec.language: \"python\"` or `spec.language: \"go\"`\n34: - **WHEN** the CodeInterpreter is parsed\n35: - **THEN** `CodeInterpreter.Spec.Language` SHALL be populated with the language identifier\n36: \n37: #### Scenario: Execution policy configuration\n38: \n39: - **GIVEN** `spec.executionPolicy` with `timeout: \"30s\"` and `maxRetries: 3`\n40: - **WHEN** the CodeInterpreter is parsed\n41: - **THEN** `ExecutionPolicy.Timeout` (metav1.Duration) and `ExecutionPolicy.MaxRetries` (int32) SHALL be populated\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: Resource quota binding\n44: \n45: - **GIVEN** `spec.resources` specifies `cpu: \"500m\"`, `memory: \"512Mi\"`, `storage: \"1Gi\"`\n46: - **WHEN** the CodeInterpreter is validated by the scheme\n47: - **THEN** `Resources` SHALL be of type `ResourceQuota` with parsed values\n48: \n49: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreter status subresource\n50: \n51: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterStatus` with `Phase` (CodeInterpreterPhase), `Conditions` ([]CodeInterpreterCondition), `Result` (string), `ExecutionTime` (metav1.Duration), and `LastTransitionTime` (metav1.Time). `CodeInterpreter` SHALL expose `.status` via the status subresource.\n52: \n53: #### Scenario: Status phase transitions\n54: \n55: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `status.phase = \"Pending\"`\n56: - **WHEN** the controller updates status to `\"Running\"` then to `\"Succeeded\"`\n57: - **THEN** `LastTransitionTime` SHALL be updated for each transition and Conditions appended\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: Condition management\n60: \n61: - **GIVEN** a condition of type `\"Ready\"` with `status: \"True\"`, `reason: \"ExecutionComplete\"`, `message: \"Code executed successfully\"`\n62: - **WHEN** status is updated via the status subresource\n63: - **THEN** the condition SHALL be upserted into `status.conditions` with `lastTransitionTime` set\n64: \n65: #### Scenario: Execution result storage\n66: \n67: - **GIVEN** code execution completes with output\n68: - **WHEN** the controller sets `status.result` to the execution output\n69: - **THEN** `status.result` SHALL contain the stdout/stderr of code execution\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: Execution time tracking\n72: \n73: - **GIVEN** code execution takes 5.2 seconds\n74: - **WHEN** the controller updates `status.executionTime`\n75: - **THEN** `status.executionTime.Duration` SHALL be `5.2s`\n76: \n77: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreter phase and condition types\n78: \n79: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterPhase` constants: `Pending`, `Running`, `Succeeded`, `Failed`, `Terminating`. The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterConditionType` constants: `Ready`, `Executing`, `Completed`.\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: Phase constant availability\n82: \n83: - **GIVEN** the `v1alpha1` package is imported\n84: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterPhaseRunning` is referenced\n85: - **THEN** it SHALL equal `\"Running\"`\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: Condition type constant availability\n88: \n89: - **GIVEN** the `v1alpha1` package is imported\n90: - **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterConditionReady` is referenced\n91: - **THEN** it SHALL equal `\"Ready\"`\n92: \n93: #### Scenario: Condition structure\n94: \n95: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterCondition` is created\n96: - **WHEN** fields are set: `Type`, `Status`, `Reason`, `Message`, `LastTransitionTime`\n97: - **THEN** the condition SHALL match the structure of `AgentRuntimeCondition`\n98: \n99: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreter validation\n100: \n101: The system SHALL implement `ValidateCodeInterpreter(obj *CodeInterpreter) field.ErrorList` in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/validation.go`. Validation SHALL check: `runtimeRef` is non-empty, `code` is non-empty, `language` is valid (python, go, nodejs), `resources` are valid quantities.\n102: \n103: #### Scenario: Valid CodeInterpreter validation\n104: \n105: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `runtimeRef: \"python-3.11\"`, `code: \"print('hello')\"`, `language: \"python\"`\n106: - **WHEN** `ValidateCodeInterpreter` is called\n107: - **THEN** `field.ErrorList` SHALL be empty\n108: \n109: #### Scenario: Missing runtimeRef validation\n110: \n111: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with empty `runtimeRef`\n112: - **WHEN** `ValidateCodeInterpreter` is called\n113: - **THEN** `field.ErrorList` SHALL contain an error for `spec.runtimeRef` with reason `Required`\n114: \n115: #### Scenario: Missing code validation\n116: \n117: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with empty `code`\n118: - **WHEN** `ValidateCodeInterpreter` is called\n119: - **THEN** `field.ErrorList` SHALL contain an error for `spec.code` with reason `Required`\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: Invalid language validation\n122: \n123: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `language: \"invalid\"`\n124: - **WHEN** `ValidateCodeInterpreter` is called\n125: - **THEN** `field.ErrorList` SHALL contain an error for `spec.language` with reason `NotSupported`\n126: \n127: #### Scenario: Invalid resource quantity validation\n128: \n129: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `resources.cpu: \"invalid\"`\n130: - **WHEN** `ValidateCodeInterpreter` is called\n131: - **THEN** `field.ErrorList` SHALL contain an error for `spec.resources.cpu` with reason `Invalid`\n132: \n133: #### Scenario: Status update phase transition validation\n134: \n135: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `status.phase = \"Succeeded\"`\n136: - **WHEN** controller attempts to update phase to `\"Running\"` via `ValidateCodeInterpreterStatusUpdate`\n137: - **THEN** `field.ErrorList` SHALL contain a `Forbidden` error for invalid phase transition\n138: \n139: ### Requirement: CRD manifest generation\n140: \n141: The system SHALL generate `manifests/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml` via `make gen-crd` using controller-gen.\n142: \n143: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter CRD with status subresource\n144: \n145: - **GIVEN** `+genclient` and `+kubebuilder:subresource:status` markers on `CodeInterpreter`\n146: - **WHEN** `make gen-crd` runs controller-gen\n147: - **THEN** the CRD manifest SHALL include `spec.subresources.status: {}`\n148: \n149: #### Scenario: CRD schema validation for required fields\n150: \n151: - **GIVEN** `+kubebuilder:validation:Required` markers on `runtimeRef` and `code`\n152: - **WHEN** CRDs are generated\n153: - **THEN** the OpenAPI v3 schema SHALL mark `runtimeRef` and `code` as required\n154: \n155: #### Scenario: CRD group and version\n156: \n157: - **GIVEN** `SchemeGroupVersion = schema.GroupVersion{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\"}`\n158: - **WHEN** CRDs render\n159: - **THEN** `metadata.name` SHALL be `codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` and `spec.group = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"`\n160: \n161: #### Scenario: CRD printer columns\n162: \n163: - **GIVEN** `+kubebuilder:printcolumn` markers on `CodeInterpreter`\n164: - **WHEN** CRDs are generated\n165: - **THEN** the CRD SHALL include printer columns for NAME, PHASE, RUNTIME, and AGE\n166: \n167: ### Requirement: client-go typed client for CodeInterpreter\n168: \n169: The system SHALL generate typed client under `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` with `CodeInterpreterInterface` providing `Create`, `Update`, `UpdateStatus`, `Delete`, `Get`, `List`, `Watch`, `Patch` methods.\n170: \n171: #### Scenario: Create CodeInterpreter via typed client\n172: \n173: - **GIVEN** a configured `Clientset` and valid `CodeInterpreter` object\n174: - **WHEN** `clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(\"default\").Create(ctx, ci, metav1.CreateOptions{})` is called\n175: - **THEN** the CodeInterpreter SHALL be created via the K8s API and returned with populated metadata\n176: \n177: #### Scenario: Update status via typed client\n178: \n179: - **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter with a mutable status\n180: - **WHEN** `UpdateStatus(ctx, ci, metav1.UpdateOptions{})` is called\n181: - **THEN** only the status subresource SHALL be updated\n182: \n183: #### Scenario: List with label selector\n184: \n185: - **GIVEN** CodeInterpreters with labels `app=runner` in namespace `default`\n186: - **WHEN** `List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{LabelSelector: \"app=runner\"})` is called\n187: - **THEN** only matching CodeInterpreters SHALL be returned\n188: \n189: #### Scenario: Watch for changes\n190: \n191: - **GIVEN** a watch on `CodeInterpreters(\"default\")`\n192: - **WHEN** a CodeInterpreter is created or updated\n193: - **THEN** the watch channel SHALL receive an `Event` with `Type` and `Object`\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: Delete by name\n196: \n197: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter named `exec-1` exists\n198: - **WHEN** `Delete(ctx, \"exec-1\", metav1.DeleteOptions{})` is called\n199: - **THEN** the CodeInterpreter SHALL be deleted from the API server\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: Patch update\n202: \n203: - **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter\n204: - **WHEN** `Patch(ctx, \"exec-1\", types.MergePatchType, data, metav1.PatchOptions{})` is called\n205: - **THEN** the CodeInterpreter SHALL be partially updated with patch data\n206: \n207: ### Requirement: Informer factory for CodeInterpreter\n208: \n209: The system SHALL generate informer under `client-go/informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` with `CodeInterpreterInformer` and methods `Informer()`, `Lister()`, `NewCodeInterpreterInformer`, `NewFilteredCodeInterpreterInformer`.\n210: \n211: #### Scenario: Start informer for CodeInterpreters\n212: \n213: - **GIVEN** a configured `SharedInformerFactory`\n214: - **WHEN** `factory.Runtime().V1alpha1().CodeInterpreters().Informer()` is called and `factory.Start(stopCh)` runs\n215: - **THEN** the informer SHALL list-watch `codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` and populate its cache\n216: \n217: #### Scenario: Event handlers for CodeInterpreter\n218: \n219: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter informer with `AddEventHandler` registered\n220: - **WHEN** a CodeInterpreter is created\n221: - **THEN** the `OnAdd` callback SHALL be invoked with the new object\n222: \n223: #### Scenario: Namespace-filtered informer\n224: \n225: - **GIVEN** `NewFilteredSharedInformerFactory` with namespace `production`\n226: - **WHEN** the factory starts\n227: - **THEN** the CodeInterpreter informer SHALL only watch CodeInterpreters in `production` namespace\n228: \n229: #### Scenario: Lister access from informer\n230: \n231: - **GIVEN** a synced CodeInterpreter informer\n232: - **WHEN** `informer.Lister().Get(\"exec-1\")` is called\n233: - **THEN** the CodeInterpreter SHALL be returned from the local cache\n234: \n235: ### Requirement: Lister for CodeInterpreter\n236: \n237: The system SHALL generate `CodeInterpreterLister` and `CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister` under `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` with `List(selector)` and `Get(name)` methods.\n238: \n239: #### Scenario: List all CodeInterpreters\n240: \n241: - **GIVEN** a populated informer cache\n242: - **WHEN** `lister.List(labels.Everything())` is called\n243: - **THEN** all CodeInterpreters SHALL be returned from the cache\n244: \n245: #### Scenario: Get by name and namespace\n246: \n247: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter named `exec-1` in namespace `default` exists in cache\n248: - **WHEN** `lister.CodeInterpreters(\"default\").Get(\"exec-1\")` is called\n249: - **THEN** the CodeInterpreter SHALL be returned or `NotFound` error if absent\n250: \n251: #### Scenario: List with label filter\n252: \n253: - **GIVEN** CodeInterpreters with various labels in cache\n254: - **WHEN** `lister.List(labels.SelectorFromSet(labels.Set{\"type\": \"batch\"}))` is called\n255: - **THEN** only CodeInterpreters matching the label selector SHALL be returned\n256: \n257: ### Requirement: Fake clients for CodeInterpreter testing\n258: \n259: The system SHALL generate fake clients under `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_codeinterpreter.go` implementing `CodeInterpreterInterface` for unit testing.\n260: \n261: #### Scenario: Unit test with fake client\n262: \n263: - **GIVEN** `fake.NewSimpleClientset()` is called\n264: - **WHEN** `Create`, `Get`, `Update`, `Delete` are called on `fake.CodeInterpreters(\"default\")`\n265: - **THEN** operations SHALL succeed in-memory without contacting K8s API\n266: \n267: #### Scenario: Reactor for error injection\n268: \n269: - **GIVEN** a fake client with `PrependReactor(\"create\", \"codeinterpreters\", ...)` that returns an error\n270: - **WHEN** `Create` is called on `CodeInterpreters(\"default\")`\n271: - **THEN** the reactor SHALL intercept and return the injected error\n272: \n273: #### Scenario: Fake client pre-population\n274: \n275: - **GIVEN** a fake client created with `NewSimpleClientset(&existingCodeInterpreter)`\n276: - **WHEN** `Get(ctx, \"exec-1\", metav1.GetOptions{})` is called\n277: - **THEN** the pre-populated CodeInterpreter SHALL be returned\n278: \n279: ### Requirement: Deepcopy generation for CodeInterpreter\n280: \n281: The system SHALL generate `DeepCopy`, `DeepCopyInto`, `DeepCopyObject` methods for `CodeInterpreter`, `CodeInterpreterSpec`, `CodeInterpreterStatus`, `CodeInterpreterList` in `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` via `make gen-deepcopy`.\n282: \n283: #### Scenario: DeepCopy for CodeInterpreter\n284: \n285: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` object with populated spec and status\n286: - **WHEN** `DeepCopy()` is called\n287: - **THEN** a new `CodeInterpreter` SHALL be returned with all fields deeply copied\n288: \n289: #### Scenario: DeepCopy for CodeInterpreterSpec\n290: \n291: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterSpec` with nested `ExecutionPolicy` and `ResourceQuota`\n292: - **WHEN** `DeepCopy()` is called\n293: - **THEN** all nested pointers SHALL be newly allocated\n294: \n295: #### Scenario: DeepCopyObject for runtime.Object interface\n296: \n297: - **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` used as `runtime.Object`\n298: - **WHEN** `DeepCopyObject()` is called\n299: - **THEN** the method SHALL return `runtime.Object` with a deep copy of the CodeInterpreter\n300: \n301: ### Requirement: Expansion interfaces for CodeInterpreter\n302: \n303: The system SHALL generate empty expansion interfaces `CodeInterpreterExpansion` in `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/generated_expansion.go` and `CodeInterpreterListerExpansion` in `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/expansion_generated.go`.\n304: \n305: #### Scenario: Client expansion interface\n306: \n307: - **GIVEN** the generated `CodeInterpreterExpansion` interface\n308: - **WHEN** a developer extends it with custom methods\n309: - **THEN** custom methods SHALL be available on `CodeInterpreterInterface` without regeneration\n310: \n311: #### Scenario: Lister expansion interface\n312: \n313: - **GIVEN** the generated `CodeInterpreterListerExpansion` interface\n314: - **WHEN** a developer extends it with custom lister methods\n315: - **THEN** custom methods SHALL be available on `CodeInterpreterLister` without regeneration\n316: \n317: ### Requirement: Scheme and codec registration for CodeInterpreter\n318: \n319: The system SHALL register CodeInterpreter types in `client-go/clientset/versioned/scheme/register.go` with `AddToScheme` functions for the generated client.\n320: \n321: #### Scenario: Scheme registration at client init\n322: \n323: - **GIVEN** the `client-go` package is imported\n324: - **WHEN** `scheme.AddToScheme(runtimeScheme)` is called\n325: - **THEN** `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` types SHALL be recognizable by the scheme\n326: \n327: #### Scenario: Negotiated serializer for CodeInterpreter\n328: \n329: - **GIVEN** a REST client with `NegotiatedSerializer`\n330: - **WHEN** encoding/decoding is needed for CodeInterpreter\n331: - **THEN** `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` SHALL be supported with `application/json`\n332: \n333: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreter resource plural\n334: \n335: The system SHALL use `codeinterpreters` as the REST resource plural for CodeInterpreter in client-go generated code.\n336: \n337: #### Scenario: Resource plural in typed client\n338: \n339: - **GIVEN** the generated `codeinterpreter.go` typed client\n340: - **WHEN** the REST client is configured\n341: - **THEN** `Resource(\"codeinterpreters\")` SHALL be used for API path construction\n342: \n343: #### Scenario: Resource plural in lister\n344: \n345: - **GIVEN** the generated `codeinterpreter.go` lister\n346: - **WHEN** `NewCodeInterpreterLister` is called\n347: - **THEN** it SHALL use `Resource(\"codeinterpreter\").GroupResource()` for the lister\n\n(End of file - total 347 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-002 — CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义 Delta Specification\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the CodeInterpreter CRD type implementation including Go API types, validation, CRD manifests, client-go library, informers, and listers for the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreter API type definition\n\nThe system SHALL define `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` with `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterSpec` types. `CodeInterpreterSpec` SHALL include `runtimeRef` (string), `code` (string), `language` (string), `executionPolicy` (ExecutionPolicy), and `resources` (ResourceQuota). `CodeInterpreter` SHALL embed `metav1.TypeMeta` and `metav1.ObjectMeta`.\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter type registration\n\n- **GIVEN** the `v1alpha1` package is imported\n- **WHEN** `SchemeBuilder.Register(&CodeInterpreter{}, &CodeInterpreterList{})` is called during init\n- **THEN** `CodeInterpreter` SHALL be registered in the scheme with `Kind = \"CodeInterpreter\"`, `APIVersion = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Runtime reference binding\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775868063395,"end":1775868063414}}}}
