{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868239511,"sessionID":"ses_28604276bffe3aMZ50oXCQRdNM","part":{"id":"prt_d79fda69b001AcnOoQi2MQmTCf","messageID":"msg_d79fd94f5001Ryo4Zmf0pF3QjV","sessionID":"ses_28604276bffe3aMZ50oXCQRdNM","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_de1c16204860439d96579213","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Specification — AR-022: CLI publish 命令\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** L  \n**Type:** Implementation of publish command for agent deployment to Kubernetes (AgentRuntime CR or standard Deployment/Service)\n\n**Base Specs:** cli-toolkit/design.md, cli-toolkit/spec.md\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-022.1: Publish Command CLI Interface\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL implement the `publish` Typer subcommand with options for workspace, version, image repository credentials, deployment region, cloud provider, provider type (agentcube/k8s), node port, replicas, namespace, and verbose logging.\n\n#### Scenario: Publish command registration\n- **GIVEN** the Typer app is initialized\n- **WHEN** the CLI loads\n- **THEN** the `publish` subcommand SHALL be registered as `agentcube publish`\n\n#### Scenario: Default workspace resolution\n- **GIVEN** user runs `agentcube publish` without `-f` flag\n- **WHEN** the command executes\n- **THEN** workspace SHALL resolve to current directory `\".\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Version specification\n- **GIVEN** user specifies `--version 1.2.3`\n- **WHEN** the command executes\n- **THEN** version SHALL override metadata version for publishing\n\n#### Scenario: Image repository URL\n- **GIVEN** user specifies `--image-url registry.example.com/myimage`\n- **WHEN** the command executes in local build mode\n- **THEN** image URL SHALL be used for image push target\n\n#### Scenario: Image repository credentials\n- **GIVEN** user specifies `--image-username` and `--image-password`\n- **WHEN** the command executes\n- **THEN** credentials SHALL be used for Docker login to image repository\n\n#### Scenario: Provider selection\n- **GIVEN** user specifies `--provider k8s`\n- **WHEN** the command executes\n- **THEN** deployment SHALL use standard Kubernetes Deployment + NodePort Service\n\n#### Scenario: Default AgentCube provider\n- **GIVEN** user does not specify `--provider`\n- **WHEN** the command executes\n- **THEN** provider SHALL default to `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR)\n\n#### Scenario: NodePort specification\n- **GIVEN** user specifies `--node-port 30080` with `--provider k8s`\n- **WHEN** the command executes\n- **THEN** Kubernetes Service SHALL use specified NodePort (30000-32767)\n\n#### Scenario: Replicas specification\n- **GIVEN** user specifies `--replicas 3` with `--provider k8s`\n- **WHEN** the command executes\n- **THEN** Deployment SHALL be created with 3 replicas\n\n#### Scenario: Namespace specification\n- **GIVEN** user specifies `--namespace production`\n- **WHEN** the command executes\n- **THEN** deployment SHALL target the `production` namespace\n\n#### Scenario: Command-level verbose logging\n- **GIVEN** user specifies `--verbose` on publish command\n- **WHEN** the command executes\n- **THEN** logging level SHALL be DEBUG for publish operation only\n\n---\n\n### REQ-022.2: PublishRuntime Integration\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL instantiate `PublishRuntime` with verbose flag and provider, and invoke `publish()` method with workspace path and options.\n\n#### Scenario: PublishRuntime instantiation\n- **GIVEN** publish command is invoked\n- **WHEN** command handler runs\n- **THEN** `PublishRuntime(verbose=verbose, provider=provider)` SHALL be instantiated\n\n#### Scenario: Pass options to PublishRuntime.publish\n- **GIVEN** CLI options are parsed\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish()` is called\n- **THEN** options dict SHALL include: `version`, `image_url`, `image_username`, `image_password`, `description`, `region`, `cloud_provider`, `node_port`, `replicas`, `namespace`\n\n#### Scenario: Handle PublishRuntime exceptions\n- **GIVEN** `PublishRuntime.publish()` raises an exception\n- **WHEN** exception is caught\n- **THEN** `_handle_error(e, \"publish\", verbose)` SHALL be invoked\n\n#### Scenario: Display publish success\n- **GIVEN** publish completes successfully\n- **WHEN** `PublishRuntime.publish()` returns result dict\n- **THEN** CLI SHALL print success message with agent endpoint and status using Rich formatting\n\n---\n\n### REQ-022.3: AgentCube Provider Prerequisites\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL validate that metadata contains required URLs for AgentCube provider deployment.\n\n#### Scenario: Router URL requirement\n- **GIVEN** provider is `agentcube`\n- **WHEN** metadata lacks `router_url`\n- **THEN** system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentCube provider requires router_url in agent_metadata.yaml\")`\n\n#### Scenario: Workload manager URL requirement\n- **GIVEN** provider is `agentcube`\n- **WHEN** metadata lacks `workload_manager_url`\n- **THEN** system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"AgentCube provider requires workload_manager_url in agent_metadata.yaml\")`\n\n#### Scenario: Both URLs present\n- **GIVEN** metadata contains both `router_url` and `workload_manager_url`\n- **WHEN** AgentCube publish proceeds\n- **THEN** validation SHALL pass\n\n---\n\n### REQ-022.4: Image Preparation Flow\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL prepare the container image for publishing via Docker push (local mode) or use explicit image URL.\n\n#### Scenario: Local image preparation with Docker push\n- **GIVEN** build mode is `local` and no `--image-url` provided\n- **WHEN** `_prepare_local_image()` runs\n- **THEN** system SHALL push image to registry using `DockerService.push_image()`\n\n#### Scenario: Image URL without credentials\n- **GIVEN** `--image-url` is provided but no credentials\n- **WHEN** image preparation runs\n- **THEN** system SHALL assume image is already pushed and use provided URL\n\n#### Scenario: Image URL with credentials\n- **GIVEN** `--image-url`, `--image-username`, and `--image-password` are provided\n- **WHEN** image preparation runs\n- **THEN** system SHALL login, tag, and push image to specified URL\n\n#### Scenario: Cloud image preparation\n- **GIVEN** build mode is `cloud`\n- **WHEN** `_prepare_cloud_image()` runs\n- **THEN** system SHALL use cloud provider's image registry URL\n\n#### Scenario: Image tag from version\n- **GIVEN** metadata version is `1.2.3`\n- **WHEN** image is prepared\n- **THEN** image tag SHALL be `{agent_name}:1.2.3`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-022.5: AgentCube CR Deployment\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL deploy AgentRuntime CR using `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()` when provider is `agentcube`.\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime CR creation\n- **GIVEN** provider is `agentcube` and prerequisites are met\n- **WHEN** `_publish_cr_to_k8s()` runs\n- **THEN** `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime()` SHALL be called with agent spec\n\n#### Scenario: Readiness probe configuration\n- **GIVEN** metadata contains `readiness_probe_path` and `readiness_probe_port`\n- **WHEN** AgentRuntime CR is created\n- **THEN** readiness probe SHALL be configured in CR spec\n\n#### Scenario: Environment variable injection\n- **GIVEN** metadata contains `workload_manager_url` and `router_url`\n- **WHEN** AgentRuntime CR is created\n- **THEN** env vars `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` and `ROUTER_URL` SHALL be set in pod spec\n\n#### Scenario: Session timeout configuration\n- **GIVEN** AgentRuntime CR is created\n- **WHEN** CR spec is assembled\n- **THEN** `sessionTimeout` SHALL be set to `\"15m\"` and `maxSessionDuration` to `\"8h\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Image pull secret reference\n- **GIVEN** AgentRuntime CR is created\n- **WHEN** CR spec is assembled\n- **THEN** `imagePullSecrets` SHALL reference `[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime CR update\n- **GIVEN** AgentRuntime CR already exists\n- **WHEN** publish is run again\n- **THEN** existing CR SHALL be patched/updated rather than recreated\n\n---\n\n### REQ-022.6: Standard Kubernetes Deployment\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL deploy standard Kubernetes Deployment + NodePort Service using `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()` when provider is `k8s`.\n\n#### Scenario: Kubernetes deployment creation\n- **GIVEN** provider is `k8s`\n- **WHEN** `_publish_k8s()` runs\n- **THEN** `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent()` SHALL be called with deployment spec\n\n#### Scenario: NodePort allocation\n- **GIVEN** user specifies `--node-port 30080`\n- **WHEN** Service is created\n- **THEN** Service SHALL use specified NodePort\n\n#### Scenario: Auto NodePort allocation\n- **GIVEN** user does not specify `--node-port`\n- **WHEN** Service is created\n- **THEN** Kubernetes SHALL allocate ephemeral NodePort (30000-32767)\n\n#### Scenario: Replica count\n- **GIVEN** user specifies `--replicas 3`\n- **WHEN** Deployment is created\n- **THEN** Deployment spec SHALL have `replicas: 3`\n\n#### Scenario: Default replica count\n- **GIVEN** user does not specify `--replicas`\n- **WHEN** Deployment is created\n- **THEN** Deployment SHALL have `replicas: 1`\n\n#### Scenario: Deployment readiness wait\n- **GIVEN** Deployment is created\n- **WHEN** publish proceeds\n- **THEN** `wait_for_deployment_ready(name, timeout=120)` SHALL be called\n\n#### Scenario: Deployment readiness timeout\n- **GIVEN** Deployment does not become ready within 120 seconds\n- **WHEN** wait completes\n- **THEN** system SHALL raise `TimeoutError(\"Deployment not ready after 120s\")`\n\n#### Scenario: Service URL reporting\n- **GIVEN** Service is created with NodePort 30080\n- **WHEN** publish completes\n- **THEN** result SHALL include `service_url: \"http://localhost:30080\"`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-022.7: Namespace Management\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL ensure target namespace exists before deployment.\n\n#### Scenario: Namespace creation\n- **GIVEN** target namespace does not exist\n- **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace()` runs\n- **THEN** namespace SHALL be created via Kubernetes API\n\n#### Scenario: Namespace already exists\n- **GIVEN** target namespace exists\n- **WHEN** `_ensure_namespace()` runs\n- **THEN** no-op SHALL occur\n\n#### Scenario: Default namespace\n- **GIVEN** user does not specify `--namespace`\n- **WHEN** deployment proceeds\n- **THEN** namespace SHALL default to `\"default\"`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-022.8: Publish Metadata Update\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL update workspace metadata with deployment information after successful publish.\n\n#### Scenario: Agent ID assignment\n- **GIVEN** AgentRuntime CR is created successfully\n- **WHEN** `_update_publish_metadata()` runs\n- **THEN** metadata `agent_id` SHALL be set to CR name\n\n#### Scenario: Agent endpoint recording\n- **GIVEN** deployment completes with service URL\n- **WHEN** metadata is updated\n- **THEN** metadata `agent_endpoint` SHALL be set to service URL\n\n#### Scenario: Session ID generation\n- **GIVEN** publish completes\n- **WHEN** metadata is updated\n- **THEN** metadata `session_id` SHALL be generated or preserved\n\n#### Scenario: Deployment info recording\n- **GIVEN** k8s provider deployment completes\n- **WHEN** metadata is updated\n- **THEN** metadata `k8s_deployment` SHALL include deployment name, service name, namespace, node_port\n\n#### Scenario: Metadata persistence\n- **GIVEN** metadata updates are made\n- **WHEN** `_update_publish_metadata()` completes\n- **THEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` SHALL be written with `yaml.dump(exclude_none=True)`\n\n---\n\n### REQ-022.9: Publish Status Reporting\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL report publish results with deployment status, agent endpoint, and next steps.\n\n#### Scenario: Publish success output\n- **GIVEN** publish completes successfully\n- **WHEN** result is returned\n- **THEN** CLI SHALL print:\n  ```\n  ✓ Publish completed successfully\n  Agent: {agent_name}\n  Provider: {provider}\n  Endpoint: {agent_endpoint}\n  Status: {status}\n  ```\n\n#### Scenario: AgentCube provider success\n- **GIVEN** AgentRuntime CR is deployed\n- **WHEN** publish completes\n- **THEN** output SHALL include CR name and namespace\n\n#### Scenario: K8s provider success\n- **GIVEN** Deployment + Service are deployed\n- **WHEN** publish completes\n- **THEN** output SHALL include service URL and node port\n\n#### Scenario: Next step guidance\n- **GIVEN** publish succeeds\n- **WHEN** output is printed\n- **THEN** CLI SHALL suggest next command: `agentcube invoke` with appropriate flags\n\n---\n\n### REQ-022.10: Error Handling\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL handle publish failures with appropriate error messages and exit codes.\n\n#### Scenario: AgentCube provider prerequisite failure\n- **GIVEN** metadata lacks router_url\n- **WHEN** publish validation runs\n- **THEN** system SHALL print error in red and exit with code 1\n\n#### Scenario: Image push failure\n- **GIVEN** Docker push fails (auth error, network error)\n- **WHEN** image preparation runs\n- **THEN** error SHALL be reported and exit code 1 returned\n\n#### Scenario: Kubernetes API failure\n- **GIVEN** Kubernetes API is unreachable\n- **WHEN** deployment is attempted\n- **THEN** error SHALL be reported and exit code 1 returned\n\n#### Scenario: Deployment readiness failure\n- **GIVEN** Deployment fails to become ready\n- **WHEN** wait timeout expires\n- **THEN** error SHALL include pod events and exit code 1\n\n#### Scenario: CRD not installed\n- **GIVEN** provider is `agentcube` but CRD not installed\n- **WHEN** CR creation is attempted\n- **THEN** error SHALL indicate CRD is missing and exit with code 1\n\n---\n\n## Data Types\n\n```python\n# Publish command options\nclass PublishOptions(TypedDict, total=False):\n    workspace: str\n    version: Optional[str]\n    image_url: Optional[str]\n    image_username: Optional[str]\n    image_password: Optional[str]\n    description: Optional[str]\n    region: Optional[str]\n    cloud_provider: Optional[str]\n    provider: str  # \"agentcube\" or \"k8s\"\n    node_port: Optional[int]\n    replicas: Optional[int]\n    namespace: Optional[str]\n    verbose: bool\n\n# Publish result structure\nclass PublishResult(TypedDict):\n    agent_name: str\n    provider: str\n    agent_id: Optional[str]\n    agent_endpoint: str\n    status: str\n    deployment_info: Optional[Dict[str, Any]]\n    publish_time: str\n```\n\n---\n\n## CLI Flags Summary\n\n| Flag | Short | Type | Default | Description |\n|------|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--workspace` | `-f` | str | `\".\"` | Path to agent workspace |\n| `--version` | - | Optional[str] | None | Semantic version string |\n| `--image-url` | - | Optional[str] | None | Image repository URL |\n| `--image-username` | - | Optional[str] | None | Image repository username |\n| `--image-password` | - | Optional[str] | None | Image repository password |\n| `--description` | - | Optional[str] | None | Agent description |\n| `--region` | - | Optional[str] | None | Deployment region |\n| `--cloud-provider` | - | Optional[str] | None | Cloud provider name |\n| `--provider` | - | str | `\"agentcube\"` | Target provider: agentcube or k8s |\n| `--node-port` | - | Optional[int] | None | NodePort for k8s Service |\n| `--replicas` | - | Optional[int] | None | Replicas for k8s Deployment |\n| `--namespace` | - | Optional[str] | None | Kubernetes namespace |\n| `--verbose` | - | bool | False | Enable detailed logging |\n\n---\n\n## Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Description | Default |\n|----------|-------------|---------|\n| `KUBECONFIG` | Kubernetes config file | `~/.kube/config` |\n| `ROUTER_URL` | AgentCube router URL | - |\n| `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | AgentCube workload manager URL | - |\n| `DOCKER_HOST` | Docker daemon socket | system default |\n\n---\n\n## Error Codes\n\n| Error | Exit Code | Message |\n|-------|-----------|---------|\n| Missing router_url | 1 | \"AgentCube provider requires router_url in agent_metadata.yaml\" |\n| Missing workload_manager_url | 1 | \"AgentCube provider requires workload_manager_url in agent_metadata.yaml\" |\n| Image push failure | 1 | \"Failed to push image: {detail}\" |\n| Kubernetes API failure | 1 | \"Kubernetes API error: {detail}\" |\n| Deployment timeout | 1 | \"Deployment not ready after {timeout}s\" |\n| CRD not installed | 1 | \"AgentRuntime CRD not installed. Run: kubectl apply -f ...\" |\n| Invalid node-port | 1 | \"NodePort must be between 30000-32767\" |\n| Namespace creation failure | 1 | \"Failed to create namespace: {detail}\" |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `typer[all]` | >=0.9.0 | CLI framework |\n| `pydantic` | >=2.0.0 | Data validation |\n| `docker` | >=6.0.0 | Docker SDK |\n| `rich` | >=13.0.0 | Output formatting |\n| `kubernetes` | >=28.0.0 | Kubernetes client |\n| `pyyaml` | >=6.0 | Metadata handling |\n| `httpx` | >=0.24.0 | HTTP client |\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Checklist\n\n- [ ] `agentcube/cli/main.py` — publish command registered with Typer\n- [ ] `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` — PublishRuntime class implemented\n- [ ] `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` — AgentCubeProvider for CR deployment\n- [ ] `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` — KubernetesProvider for standard deployment\n- [ ] `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` — DockerService for image push\n- [ ] Image preparation flow (local push, cloud, explicit URL)\n- [ ] AgentCube CR deployment with readiness probe\n- [ ] K8s Deployment + NodePort Service deployment\n- [ ] Namespace management\n- [ ] Metadata update with deployment info\n- [ ] Success/failure output with Rich formatting\n- [ ] Verbose mode streams deployment logs\n- [ ] Error handling with appropriate exit codes\n- [ ] Next step guidance after successful publish\n- [ ] Code coverage >= 80% for publish path\n\n---\n\n## Open Questions\n\n1. Should publish command support `--dry-run` for validation without deployment?\n2. Should `--wait` flag be added to control readiness wait behavior?\n3. Should publish support `--rollback` on deployment failure?\n4. Should multi-region deployment be supported via `--region` flag?\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775868239391,"end":1775868239506}}}}
